    "what_description": "Plocama dezfulensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is a shrub that typically grows up to 60 cm in height, with simple, oppositely arranged leaves that are elliptical to lanceolate in shape, 2-5 cm in length, and have a glabrous to pubescent surface. The inflorescence is a corymb, bearing small, white flowers that are 2-3 mm in diameter, with a four-lobed calyx and a corolla that is bilabiate. The fruits are small, red or purple drupes that are 2-3 mm in length. Plocama dezfulensis is endemic to Iran, where it is found in the Dezful region.",
